// New Middle



@new_middle
subtitle: This demographic is traditionally dominated by the liberal parties. 

As a Marxist party, the SPD is eyed by government officials and white-collar workers with some suspicion. Though the new middle class is willing to work with us and we have a strong history of collaboration, this group is quite independent from the worker's movement and many even see us as being uneducated. It's up to the SPD to change these views.

What will be our campaign's message?

- @liberal_agressive: We shall embark in a campaign of relentless harassment towards the New Middle Class. SPD hecklers, mobs and fierce agitators shall roam the streets, making sure no liberal is unscathed!
- @intellectual_warfare: It's pointless to extend an olive branch to the New Middle Class, it'll never change their minds on socialism. What we need is to harshly criticize their moral failings and prove ourselves to be in the right. By humiliating the liberals and showing how they have no moral grandstanding, we can force them to accept socialism as the one true path forwards.
- @intellectual_olive_branch: We must create an atmosphere of healthy intellectual debate with hopes for the potential emerging synthesis between our viewpoints- At least a fair amount ought to learn of Marxist thought. To the universities, coffeehouses and journals we go!  
- @republican_new_middle: We will focus on pushing for meaningful changing and posing difficult questions about the monarchy and complacency, aiming to radicalize the liberals into taking action and further into the left.
- @reformist_new_middle: We will forgo electoral appeal to focus on presenting ourselves as a cooperative partner of the liberal movement, focusing on our contributions to Germany and presenting ourselves as a strong partner. 
- @liberal_new_middle: We will focus on a liberal message, emphasizing individual rights and positing trade unions and the SPD as defenders of democratic rights.
- @liberal_hijack_new_middle: We will try to hijack the liberal message from the liberal parties, trying to pose ourselves as the best choice for liberalism. 
- @start: Let's check the other demographics.

@intellectual_warfare
subtitle: Can we really change people's minds this way?

